# Force LF line endings on cross-platform tooling files. GitHub Actions
# YAML parser fails to read `workflow_dispatch` inputs when the file
# has CRLF line endings — observed empirically when contributors on
# Windows committed workflows that GH then refused to dispatch via
# `gh workflow run` (HTTP 422 "Workflow does not have 'workflow_dispatch'
# trigger"). Same root cause behind shell-script + dotfile portability.
#
# `text eol=lf` overrides core.autocrlf on the local machine and any
# `gitattributes` inheritance — explicit per-glob is the bigtech pattern
# (see github/docs, vercel/next.js, shopify/polaris .gitattributes).

# YAML — workflows, configs, schemas
*.yml      text eol=lf
*.yaml     text eol=lf

# Shell scripts — must be LF for shebang resolution and ubuntu runners
*.sh       text eol=lf

# JSON — most tooling tolerates CRLF but LF avoids confusing diffs
*.json     text eol=lf

# Markdown — keep LF so PR diffs are clean cross-OS
*.md       text eol=lf
*.mdx      text eol=lf

# TypeScript / JavaScript — Angular CLI generates LF, keep it consistent
*.ts       text eol=lf
*.tsx      text eol=lf
*.js       text eol=lf
*.mjs      text eol=lf
*.cjs      text eol=lf

# HTML / CSS / SCSS — generated by Angular CLI as LF
*.html     text eol=lf
*.css      text eol=lf
*.scss     text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize
*.png      binary
*.jpg      binary
*.jpeg     binary
*.gif      binary
*.webp     binary
*.ico      binary
*.woff     binary
*.woff2    binary
*.ttf      binary
*.eot      binary
*.pdf      binary
